        <updateDate>2025-08-12T16:25:19Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automotive Support Services to Improve Safe Transportation Act of 2025 or the ASSIST Act of 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill expands the definition of &lt;em&gt;medical services&lt;/em&gt; for purposes of veteransâ€™ benefits to include additional medically necessary automobile&amp;nbsp;adaptations. Under the bill, the Department of Veterans Affairs may provide funding for the following medically necessary automobile adaptations for driver or passenger use:&amp;nbsp;ramp and kneeling systems, lowered floors, occupied and unoccupied mobility lifts, ingress or egress accessibility modifications, and adapted seating.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The bill also extends the limitation on pension amounts for certain hospitalized or institutionalized veterans through September 30, 2032.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
